==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: sign language
<hw>sign" lang`uage</hw> <pr>(s⟦imac⟧n" l⟦acr⟧ng`w⟦asl⟧j)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A form of language for communicating by use of
gestures made by the hands, rather than by speech. It includes alphabets
made by hand gestures, as well as proper languages formed from signs.
Among the latter is the <stype>American Sign Language</stype> (ASL),
used by the deaf. See also <er>dactylology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>sign off</ent>⟦br⟧
